Spec: Extension Source

Purpose:
  Contain the TypeScript implementation and co-located tests for SpecDD language support.

Structure:
  ./extension.ts: Extension activation, provider registration, diagnostics, and commands.
  ./language.ts: Shared language constants and section metadata.
  ./parser.ts: Pure line-oriented parser and validator.
  ./parser.test.ts: Jest tests for parser and validation behavior.
  ./references.ts: Content-root, path, and related-spec resolution helpers.
  ./references.test.ts: Jest tests for reference resolution behavior.

Owns:
  ./*.ts

Can modify:
  ./*.sdd

Can read:
  ../reference/LANGUAGE.md
  ../vscode-plugin.sdd

Must:
  Put substantial behavior in same-basename specs next to the source file.
  Keep test files co-located with the code they exercise.
